But all that seems consigned to history - none of United's 13 goals this season have come after the 62 minute mark.

Radamel Falcao's winner against Everton on Sunday came just after the hour - but that is the latest they've scored so far this season.

By contrast, they have conceded eight goals beyond 62 minutes, including four at Leicester in the league and three at MK Dons in the Capital One Cup.

